{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_67","type":"agent_message","text":"The primary summary is clear enough to report: hidden categorical sampling substantially changes behavior and hurts accuracy, while SAP and Gaussian hidden sampling preserve accuracy but alter entropy/calibration. Final-softmax sampling mostly preserves accuracy at `S=20` but has much worse NLL than deterministic because empirical sampled probabilities put too little mass on the true class."}}
