{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_93","type":"agent_message","text":"Research execution is complete.\n\nPrimary deliverables:\n- [REPORT.md](/workspaces/sampling-nn-d01c-codex/REPORT.md)\n- [README.md](/workspaces/sampling-nn-d01c-codex/README.md)\n- [planning.md](/workspaces/sampling-nn-d01c-codex/planning.md)\n- [src/sampling_nn_experiment.py](/workspaces/sampling-nn-d01c-codex/src/sampling_nn_experiment.py)\n- [CODE_WALKTHROUGH.md](/workspaces/sampling-nn-d01c-codex/CODE_WALKTHROUGH.md)\n\nKey result: intermediate activation sampling does change behavior differently from final-softmax sampling. Naive categorical hidden sampling was strongly disruptive, dropping accuracy from 98.55% to 79.41% on MNIST and from 88.77% to 66.30% on Fashion-MNIST at `S=20`. SAP-style and Gaussian hidden sampling preserved accuracy almost exactly, but changed entropy, calibration, and probability variance.\n\nOutputs are saved in:\n- [results/metrics_raw.csv](/workspaces/sampling-nn-d01c-codex/results/metrics_raw.csv)\n- [results/metrics_summary.csv](/workspaces/sampling-nn-d01c-codex/results/metrics_summary.csv)\n- [results/statistical_tests.csv](/workspaces/sampling-nn-d01c-codex/results/statistical_tests.csv)\n- [figures/](/workspaces/sampling-nn-d01c-codex/figures)\n\nValidation passed:\n- 102 metric rows generated.\n- 34 summary rows generated.\n- 40 statistical test rows generated.\n- Repeat stochastic evaluation with the same seed reproduced exactly.\n- Syntax check passed for the experiment script."}}
